title: For Sale:  CHEAP Mosquito
postcontent: i know, I know.......the Mosquito is the worlds worst .22 caliber pistol. And it's because the dang thing will not cycle at all.......making it a pain in the butt single shot!!!    But if you have ever placed one in your hand......you would have to admit it becomes one-with- your-hand. Ergonomically, its very nice. Now, if it would only shoot. My my story goes like this,: I bought it new about 3 yrs ago at Academy. Because I have other pistols, it was a while before I ever shot it. When I got around to it I found out what everyone else knew.......it wouldn't cycle. I read some blogs about it and they all pointed to the sucky feed ramp. Disgusted, I put it in the safe and forgot about it. Several months ago I decided to do something about the pistol, so I called Sig. To their defense, they said that in the manual it says specifically to use only "high velocity" .22 bullets. I checked my manual and indeed, that's what it says,. But, LSS, they had me send it to them and they polished the feed ramp and some other things and sent it back to me. I loaded it up with HV bullets and it shoots perfectly......and is now a very sweet pistol.But I am selling it because I have purchased a .22 suppressor and need a threaded .22 pistol.....and no one sells one for the Mosquito. So, now you can buy this very nice shooting Mosquito that has been fixed by the Sig folks for $200 firm. I have not tried cheapo .22 ammo in it but I KNOW it cycles perfectly with the HV stuff (like Federal 1300fps).  And I know it has not had even a hundred rounds through it.i might trade something for it, but I really need to get a threaded pistol.call, txt or email. REDACTED. I actually live in Powell MO (15 miles north of Pea Ridge)oh yeah, it comes with three magazines and a cheapo Cordova holster......but it works......(and manual, case, etc)
